      "content": "The danger isn't just about the pill itself, but how your kidneys process it, and they are already weakened. Even if you felt fine before, your current kidney status changes the risk profile entirely. For a pounding headache, you need something that won't stress your kidneys, so I strongly advise against the ibuprofen. Try a cold compress on your forehead and focus on deep, slow breathing instead.",
      "source": "target",
